<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1606" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1606">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/92.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 12.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 12, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 15
                            of the 29th ultimo, reporting the conversation between yourself and Mr.
                            Augusto Dziuk, the representative of the Balboa and Pacific Estates
                            Company Limited and the Balboa and Darien Estates and Railway Company,
                            in regard to the railroad concession granted to these companies.</p>
                        <p>Copies of your despatch and the English text of the enclosure have been
                            forwarded to the Secretary of War.</p>
                        <p>The Department’s views as to this concession are covered by instruction
                            No. 89, of September 20, 1911, to Mr. Andrews.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>